Sentencas: In comparison to various power generating devices/energy conversion systems, solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) has received much attention due to its remarkable efficiency, reliability and low pollution.
Titulo: Performance evaluation of highly active and novel La0.7Sr0.3Ti0.1Fe0.6Ni0.3O3-δ material both as cathode and anode for intermediate-temperature symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Modified pechini method is used to synthesize La0.7Sr0.3Ti0.1Fe0.6Ni0.3O3-delta (LSTFN) pemvskite material and is utilized as cathode and anode for intermediate-temperature symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SSOFC).
Titulo: Performance evaluation of highly active and novel La0.7Sr0.3Ti0.1Fe0.6Ni0.3O3-δ material both as cathode and anode for intermediate-temperature symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The X-ray diffractometer (XRD) patterns reveals perovskite cubic structure with single phase for LSTFN.
Titulo: Performance evaluation of highly active and novel La0.7Sr0.3Ti0.1Fe0.6Ni0.3O3-δ material both as cathode and anode for intermediate-temperature symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The maximum conductivity similar to 318 Scm(-1) is obtained for LSTFN in air at a temperature of 700 degrees C, but is decreased with further increase in temperature due to small polaron mechanism.
Titulo: Performance evaluation of highly active and novel La0.7Sr0.3Ti0.1Fe0.6Ni0.3O3-δ material both as cathode and anode for intermediate-temperature symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: However, the conductivity is enhanced up to similar to 1.1 Scm(-1) at the same temperature in the presence of dry H-2, being capable to be utilized both as anode and cathode.
Titulo: Performance evaluation of highly active and novel La0.7Sr0.3Ti0.1Fe0.6Ni0.3O3-δ material both as cathode and anode for intermediate-temperature symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Low polarization resistance (Rp) similar to 0.047 (with air) and 0.20 Omega cm(2) (with dry H-2) is exhibited by as prepared perovskite material at a temperature of 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Performance evaluation of highly active and novel La0.7Sr0.3Ti0.1Fe0.6Ni0.3O3-δ material both as cathode and anode for intermediate-temperature symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The fabricated symmetrical cell maintains good stability with no apparent degradation during the tested hours similar to 300 in air and similar to 100 with dry H-2.
Titulo: Performance evaluation of highly active and novel La0.7Sr0.3Ti0.1Fe0.6Ni0.3O3-δ material both as cathode and anode for intermediate-temperature symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell
